ation into combat as a victory for gender equality. Jennifer Greenburg critically interrogates a new imperial feminism and its central role in securing US hegemony. Women's incorporation into combat through emotional labor has reinforced gender stereotypes, with counterinsurgency framing female soldiers as global ambassadors for women's rights. This book provides an analysis of US imperialism that keeps the present in tension with the past, clarifying where colonial ideologies of race, gender, and sexuality have resurfaced and how they are changing today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xParticipation, Female. 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021-Participation, Female. 0aCounterinsurgencyzAfghanistanxHistoryy21st century. 0aCounterinsurgencyzIraqxHistoryy21st century. 0aImperialismxSocial aspects. 0aIraq War, 2003-2011xParticipation, Female. 0aSex rolezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aWomen soldiersxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aWomen soldiers-Government policy-United States. 4aGENDER STUDIES. 4aGEOGRAPHY. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  afemale engagement teams, post 9/11 wars, gender and war, female counterinsurgency teams, female soldiers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978